article.headline: E. Michigan 68, Toledo 44
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Carlos Medlock had 20 points to lead Eastern Michigan to a 68-44 Mid-American win over Toledo on Tuesday night. Justin Dobbins added 14 and Zane Gay 10 for the Eagles (3-2, 7-10). Travis Lewis was the team's leading rebounder with seven, while Jesse Bunkley had six assists. Tyrone Kent led the Rockets (2-3, 5-12) with 16 and Jonathan Amos had nine. Eastern Michigan led by as many as 27 with about six minutes left. Eastern Michigan led 39-17 at the half. Toledo managed only five points in the game's first 10:07 and went scoreless for 6:11. That allowed the Eagles to build a 24-5 lead after Tyler Jones' layup with 10:18 left in the first half. Two free throws by Kent with 9:52 remaining in the half broke the Rockets' scoreless spell. Medlock got 14 of his points in the first half, including nine of Eastern Michigan's last 13 of the half.
